# 🚀 GitHub Profile Viewer (Android App)
A modern Android application built using Jetpack Compose that allows users to search GitHub profiles and view their repositories in a clean and interactive UI.

## ✨ Features
🔍 Search GitHub users by username
👤 View user profile (avatar, username, followers)
📦 View repositories list
⚡ Smooth navigation between screens
💾 Recent searches (stored locally)
🌐 Internet connectivity check
❌ Proper error handling (user not found, network issues)
🎨 Clean modern UI with Material 3
📱 Custom app icon

## 🛠 Tech Stack
* Kotlin
* Jetpack Compose
* MVVM Architecture
* Retrofit (API calls)
* Gson (JSON parsing)
* Coil (Image loading)
* Navigation Compose
* Coroutines

## 📂 Project Structure
com.example.githubprofileviewer
│
├── data/               # API & Retrofit
├── ui/                 # Screens (MainScreen, ProfileScreen)
│   ├── components/     # Reusable UI components
│   └── theme/          # Colors & Theme
├── utils/              # Network utilities
├── MainViewModel.kt    # Business logic
├── UiState.kt          # UI state handling

## 🧠 Architecture
This app follows MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel):
* View (UI): Jetpack Compose screens
* ViewModel: Handles business logic & API calls
* Model: API responses

## ⚙️ How It Works
1. User enters GitHub username
2. App navigates to profile screen
3. API fetches:
   * User details
   * Repositories
4. UI updates based on state:
   * Loading → Skeleton UI
   * Success → Data shown
   * Error → Friendly message

